<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10105596>
    dc:description "Figs 600–603. Galeopsomyia scarpia, holotype ♀ – (600) habitus dorsal view; (601) habitus lateral view. Galeopsomyia schefflerae, holotype ♀ – (602) habitus dorsal view; (603) habitus lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10105596/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10105693>
    dc:description "Figs 864–871. Head incl. antennae, lateral view ♀ – (864) Galeopsomyia perla; (865) G. picuda; (866) G. teronadis; (867) G. pilonensis; (868) G. schefflerae; (869) G. pyrillia; (870) G. rugosa; (871) G. weinmanniae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10105693/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10105744>
    dc:description "Figs 993–996. Head incl. antennae/body, lateral view, paratype ♂. (993) Galeopsomyia piperae; (994) G. schefflerae; (995) G. truncata; (996) G. verbesinae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10105744/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10105256>
    dc:description "Figs 23–28. Galeopsomyia spp., ♀, first gastral tergite (Gt1) dorsal view – (23) G. epidius; (24) G. osaensis; (25) G. fausta; (26) G. blakeae; (27) G. illydris; (28) G.devania." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10105256/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

